You can buy attention (advertising). You can beg for attention from the media (Fin TV). You can bug people one at a time to get attention (sales). Or you can earn attention by creating something interesting and valuable and then publishing it online for free. @tomkeene
The qualities that make Twitter seem inane and half-baked are what makes it so powerful.
On Twitter, we get excited if someone follows us. In real life, we get really scared and run away.

What you post online speaks volumes about who you really are. Post with intention. Repost with caution.@dougkass @realmoney @tomkeene @jimcramer @riskreversal @ferrotv @lisaabramowicz1 @ScottWapnerCNBC @carlquintanilla
"Feeling" is not a viable investment strategy. @dougkass Respectfully.
